{"title_page": "Jazza (YouTuber)", "text_new": "{{short description|Australian artist}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}}\n{{Infobox YouTube personality\n| name          = Jazza\n| image         =\n| image_size    = \n| caption       = \"If I had a Wikipedia page, this should definitely be the picture of me.\" -Jazza, 2018\n| channel_name = Jazza\n| birth_name    = Josiah Asian Brooks\n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|df=y|1989|4|20}}\n| birth_place   = [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]], Australia\n| residence     = [[Moe, Victoria]], Australia<ref name=\"abc millions\" />\n| occupation    = [[YouTube personality]], artist, animator, television presenter, [[video game developer]]\n| spouse        = {{marriage|Kate Brags|2014}}\n| relatives =\n| pseudonym     = \n| years_active  = 2006\u2013present\n| genre         = {{flatlist|\n* [[Art education]]\n* [[Vlog]]\n}}\n<!-- NOTE: If you update views or subscribers, please also refresh the stats_update date -->\n| views         = 2.765 billion\n| subscribers     = 5.04 million\n| stats_update    = 27 March 2020\n| silver_year     = 2014\n| gold_year       = 2017\n| silver_button   = yes\n| gold_button     = yes\n| diamond_button  = no\n}}\n\n'''Josiah Alan Brooks''' (born 20 April 1989),<ref name=\"draw my life\"/> known online as '''Jazza''' (formerly '''Draw with Jazza'''), is an Australian [[YouTuber]] artist, Web-gen{{huh|date=April 2020}} animator, and presenter best known for his art tutorials, challenges and animations. {{as of|2020|3|df=}}, his channel has over 866 million total video views and 5.04 million subscribers.\n\n== Career ==\nJosiah Brooks was born as the fifth of six children.<ref name=\"abc millions\" /> He grew up in [[Victoria, Australia]].<ref name=\"draw my life\"/> At 12 years old he became interested in art, and began practicing drawing.<ref name=\"latrobe1\" /> He used Jazza as his username and moniker for his [[Hotmail]] account.<ref name=\"hypable\" /> During high school, he began drawing and animating in [[Microsoft PowerPoint]] and [[Adobe Flash]].<ref name=\"draw my life\"/><ref name=\"abc radio\"/> He said he would look forward to spending time in the school library or lunch period where he could draw and create his own realities.<ref name=\"abc millions\" /><ref name=\"draw my life\"/>\n\nIn 2006, when he was 17, he started getting sponsorships from websites for animations, and after graduating high school, he got into producing animation and online video games.<ref name=\"abc millions\" /><ref name=\"hypable\" /> He had joined [[Newgrounds]] in 2003, and submitted his first game there in 2006.<ref name=\"newgrounds\"/> The games were developed using [[Adobe Flash]].<ref name=\"abc radio\"/><ref name=\"lifehacker\" />\n\nIn 2011, he saw that Flash animations were in decline, around the time of the \"iPhone era\".<ref name=\"hypable\" /><ref name=\"lifehacker\" /> He looked at his old YouTube channel, and noticed that his art tutorial videos had received the most views.<ref name=\"lifehacker\" /> In 2012 he created a new channel which he called ''Draw with Jazza''.<ref name=\"latrobe1\" /><ref name=\"abc radio\"/> He said, \"People go online looking for tutorials on how to draw. ... Whenever I looked there was nothing good... they had loud music and voice-overs or were slow and boring.\" He started with tutorials on drawing the [[human anatomy]].<ref name=\"latrobe1\" /> The videos were filmed with a simple webcam and microphone, and had minimal editing.<ref name=\"lifehacker\" /> His tutorials have garnered success in views and has also attracted people to his freelance animation business.<ref name=\"latrobe1\" />\n\n<!-- format and style of videos -->\n''Draw with Jazza'' videos are uploaded weekly. Topics are mainly drawing tutorials, but also include character designs, speed painting, and art competitions. He presents \"art challenges\" of various kinds. He inserts comedic commentary over his art project videos.<ref name=\"mashable\" /> He has also reviewed art software and equipment.<ref name=\"forbes\" /> His secondary channel ''Daily Jazza'' includes daily [[video log|vlogs]] where he talks with his community about major events occurring in his life,<ref name=\"lifehacker\" /> or behind the scenes looks into his projects. Other channels he has created include ''It's Tabletop Time'', launched in 2015, where he plays role-playing games with his friends;<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=U9zcq0kE1Oc |title=STREAM SCHEDULE! + Exciting New Channel! |last=Draw with Jazza |date=29 January 2015 |via=YouTube |access-date=4 October 2018}}</ref> ''JazzaStudios'', where he releases cool animated shorts; ''JosiahBrooksMusic'', for his original [[music videos]].<ref name=\"hypable\" />\n\nHe describes his art style as [[cartoon]]-like, but has also tried to extend to comic books.<ref name=\"hypable\" /><ref name=\"telangana\">{{cite web|url=https://telanganatoday.com/drawing-favourite-cartoons|title=Learn to draw your favourite cartoons|website=telanganatoday.com|accessdate=4 October 2018}}</ref> His biggest influence was Christopher Hart, an artist who authors many how-to-draw books.<ref name=\"latrobe1\" /><ref name=\"hypable\" /> He and Hart would later collaborate to manage Hart's YouTube channel.<ref name=\"latrobe1\" /> Other influences include Internet animators [[Adam Phillips (animator)|Adam Phillips]], [[Bernard Derriman]], [[James Farr]], James Lee and Johnny Utah.<ref name=\"hypable\" />\n\nIn 2014, his YouTube channel reached 100,000 subscribers.<ref name=\"latrobe1\" /> It was at this time he was able to switch to treating it as a business and doing it full-time. He received a sponsorship from the CEO of Newgrounds.<ref name=\"lifehacker\" /> In 2015, Google and [[Screen Australia]] granted Brooks AU$100,000 as part of their Skip Ahead initiative program.<ref name=\"metro screen\">{{cite web|url=http://metroscreen.org.au/five-australian-youtubers-to-share-500000-in-google-and-screen-australias-talent-development-initiative-skip-ahead/|title=Five Australian YouTubers to share $500,000 in Skip Ahead|website=[[Metro Screen]]|accessdate=4 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.screenaustralia.gov.au/sa/media-centre/news/2017/09-09-skip-ahead-turns-four |title=Skip Ahead Turns Four: $500K for Online Creators From Google and Screen Australia |publisher=[[Screen Australia]] |access-date=3 October 2018}}</ref> He joined other YouTubers in Los Angeles to work at YouTube Space and produced a series of short films titled ''The Tale Teller'',<ref name=\"latrobe2\" /><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.businessacumen.biz/news-creative-industries/1493-google-backs-skip-ahead-screen-initiative |title=Google backs Skip Ahead screen initiative |publisher=Business Acumen Magazine |access-date=3 October 2018}}</ref> which was a three-part mini-documentary that follows \"an old man who enters a city with nothing to his name but the stories he has spent his life gathering, which he wishes to pass on before he dies.\"<ref name=\"forbes 2015\" /> In 2015, ''[[Forbes]]'' contributor Don Groves reported that ''Draw with Jazza'' had 25 million views with 60% in the United States and 20% in Europe.<ref name=\"forbes 2015\" /> In 2016, ''Forbes'' contributor Rob Salkowitz reported that ''Draw with Jazza'' had 573 videos, over 45&nbsp;million views and 658,000 subscribers.<ref name=\"forbes\" /> In November 2017, [[Mashable]] reported that ''Draw with Jazza'' had two million subscribers, with 45 percent of them from the US, 12 percent from the UK, 10 from Australia, and some amount from non-English speaking countries and locations such as Germany, the Netherlands, and South America.<ref name=\"mashable\" />\n\nIn 2016, he participated in the [[Adobe Systems]]' [[Twitch (service)|Twitch]] stream session on \"Building Flexible Animation\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.twitch.tv/drawwithjazza |title=drawwithjazza |publisher=Twitch |access-date=2 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.twitch.tv/videos/70811926 |title=Draw with Jazza: Building flexible animation Pt.2: The Body! #animatecc #adobe #danceyourpantsoff |publisher=[[Twitch (service)|Twitch]] |access-date=3 October 2018}}</ref> He published the book ''Draw With Jazza \u2013 Creating Characters: Fun and Easy Guide to Drawing Cartoons and Comics''.<ref name=\"amazon\" /><ref name=\"rtve\" /> He also had a series of shorts called ''Cartoon It Up'' which was televised on [[ABC Me]] and made available on its video watching app.<ref name=\"abc me\"/><ref name=\"mumbrella\"/> He designed the [[List of Google April Fools' Day jokes#Googz|April Fools Day logo \"Googz\"]] for Google Australia in 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.techtimes.com/articles/224203/20180402/april-fools-day-2018-here-are-googles-pranks-this-year.htm|title=April Fools' Day 2018: Here Are Google's Pranks This Year|first=Ron|last=Caraos|date=2 April 2018|website=Tech Times | accessdate=4 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tubefilter.com/2018/04/02/april-fools-day-2018/|title=YouTube Channels Fine Bros Entertainment, Draw With Jazza Contribute Top April Fools Day Hijinks |first=Sam | last=Gutelle|date=2 April 2018|website=[[Tubefilter]] |accessdate=4 October 2018}}</ref>\n\nBrooks regularly attends conventions including [[PAX (event)|PAX]],{{verify source|date=October 2018}} [[VidCon]] Australia,<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.heraldsun.com.au/kids-news/news/youtube-creators-and-internet-stars-get-ready-for-vidcon-australia/news-story/365648f569be84351f4cc97731ea6987 | title=YouTube creators and internet stars get ready for VidCon Australia | first=Tamsin | last=Rose | publication-date=11 September 2017 | work=Kids News | access-date=4 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://vidconaustralia.com/people/5502/draw-with-jazza/|title=Draw with Jazza | website=[[VidCon]] | location=Australia |year=2018 | accessdate=4 October 2018}}</ref> and Comic-Con.<ref name=\"abc radio\"/>{{verify source|date=October 2018}} He says he also outsources some of his work so that other artists can make a living in the same field he does.<ref name=\"abc millions\" />\n\nIn 2019, he changed his YouTube username to Jazza.\n\n== Personal life ==\nBrooks was raised in a [[Latter-day Saint]] family, but left the church when he was 21 as he no longer agreed with its views.<ref name=\"abc millions\" /> One of his brothers, Shad M. Brooks, is a YouTuber and Author<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.shadmbrooks.com/books|title=Books|website=shadmbrooks.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref> who runs a channel called Shadiversity,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCkmMACUKpQeIxN9D9ARli1Q|title=Shadiversity|website=YouTube|language=en|access-date=2018-10-15}}</ref> which focuses on medieval and fantasy items.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.popularmechanics.com/military/weapons/a28286/early-steel-swords-history/|title=The Earliest Steel Swords Were Game Changers|author=|date=20 September 2017|website=popularmechanics.com|accessdate=28 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.clickondetroit.com/1d4/1d4-social-media/medieval-masters-shadiversity|title=Medieval Masters - Shadiversity|first=Jake|last=Draugelis|date=|website=www.clickondetroit.com|accessdate=28 October 2018}}</ref> He also draws,<ref>{{Citation|last=Shadiversity|title=Did you know I can draw?|date=2015-05-28|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-7Aw_HUV57M|access-date=2018-10-15}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=Shadiversity|title=Is the castle by DRAW WITH JAZZA realistic?  feat Jazza himself|date=2017-09-01|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iMpPB-8f2Sw|access-date=2018-10-15}}</ref> and has produced some role-playing game material with Jazza.<ref name=\"cogent\">{{cite web|url=https://cogentroleplay.com/about/|title=ABOUT - Cogent Roleplay|author=|date=|website=cogentroleplay.com|accessdate=28 October 2018}}</ref>\n\n<!-- per [[WP:BLPPRIVACY]], do not list names of children until he publicizes them fully, which he has not as of 13 October 2018 -->\nBrooks is married and has two children: a son born in 2015<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/1zW_ChsBpx/ |title=My first employee. He's cheap, but is behind on his deadlines. Get your act together kid! ;) |last=Jazza |date=22 April 2015 |via=[[Instagram]] |access-date=3 October 2018}}</ref> and a daughter born in 2018.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BoXZ_BJgj23/ |title=Off to meet my daughter for the first time! \ud83d\udc96 |last=Jazza |date=30 September 2018 |via=[[Instagram]] |access-date=3 October 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Books ==\n* ''Draw With Jazza \u2013 Creating Characters: Fun and Easy Guide to Drawing Cartoons and Comics'' (Impact Books, 2016) {{ISBN|978-1440344947}}<ref name=\"amazon\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.amazon.com/Draw-Jazza-Creating-Characters-Cartoons/dp/1440344949 |title=Draw With Jazza \u2013 Creating Characters: Fun and Easy Guide to Drawing Cartoons and Comics |date=8 November 2016 |publisher=IMPACT Books |access-date=3 October 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"rtve\"/><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.barnesandnoble.com/w/draw-with-jazza-characters-josiah-brooks/1123371054?ean=9781440344947&st=PLA&sid=BNB_DRS_New+Core+Shopping+Top+Margin+EANs_00000000&2sid=Google_&sourceId=PLGoP210227&gclid=Cj0KCQjw0dHdBRDEARIsAHjZYYCMYJAeoNURxCKydFlAU8InUyeWvF0GY0dDKzHUWxiUQDs20DvNVdcaAqKsEALw_wcB#/ |title=Draw With Jazza \u2013 Characters: Anatomy, expressions and poses for cartoons and comics |publisher=F+W Media |via=Barnes and Noble |access-date=3 October 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Other works ==\n* ''Cartoon It Up'' \u2013 2016 television series shorts broadcast on [[ABC Me]] and ABC iview.<ref name=\"abc me\">{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.net.au/tv/programs/cartoon-it-up/|title=Cartoon It Up|work=[[ABC Television]]|location=Australia|accessdate=4 October 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"mumbrella\" />\n* ''Jazza's Arty Games'' \u2013 phone and computer application<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://jazzastudios.com/product/arty-games/ |title=Jazza's Arty Games! (PC App) |publisher=Jazza Studios |access-date=2 October 2018}}</ref>\n* ''Stand out and make money on YouTube!'' \u2013 online course on [[Skillshare]]<ref name=\"skillshare\" />\n* ''How to Talk and Present to Camera like a Pro!'' \u2013 online course on Skillshare<ref name=\"skillshare\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.skillshare.com/user/jazza |title=Josiah (Jazza) Brooks |website=[[Skillshare]] |access-date=3 October 2018}}</ref>\n* ''Jazza's Coloring eBook!'' \u2013 digital coloring book (2017)<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://jazzastudios.com/product/colorbook/ |title=Jazza's Coloring eBook! |publisher=Jazza Studios |access-date=8 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=402_wUkJM9c|title=OUT NOW! Jazza's Coloring eBook!|first=|last=Draw with Jazza|date=22 December 2017|publisher=|accessdate=13 October 2018|via=YouTube}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|refs=\n\n<ref name=\"abc millions\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2018-05-01/draw-with-jazza-josiah-brooks-youtube-fame/9690768 |title=''Draw with Jazza'': The YouTube star teaching millions from his garage in regional Victoria |last=Symons |first=Bec |publisher=[[ABC News (Australia)|ABC News]] | location=Australia | publication-date=30 April 2018 |access-date=3 October 2018}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"abc radio\">{{cite interview|url=http://www.abc.net.au/radio/melbourne/programs/breakfast/jazza-aka-josiah-brooks/8884648|title=Draw with Jazza: The YouTube star making art accessible\"| work=On Breakfast with Jacinta Parsons and Sami Shah |publisher=[[ABC Radio Melbourne]] | medium=article and online audio | interviewer=Jacinta Parsons ; [[Sami Shah]] | first=Josiah | last=Brooks  | publication-date=8 September 2017 | access-date=3 October 2018 }}</ref>{{verify source|reason=needs to verify whether he said all those things that were added to the article|date=October 2018}}\n\n<ref